le%20giving%20antibiotics.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Flife-style%2Fhealth-fitness%2Fhealth-news%2Fhealth-ministry-asks-doctors-to-mention-the-reason-for-prescribing-antibiotics%2Farticleshow%2F106948440.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22There%20Was%20A%20Time%20When%201%20Dollar%20Was%20Less%20Than%20Rs%205%3A%20Know%20History%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20dollar%20is%20one%20of%20the%20strongest%20currencies%20in%20the%20world.%20Most%20of%20the%20global%20trade%20is%20pegged%20to%20the%20dollar%2C%20since%20it%20is%20among%20the%20safest%20currencies%20in%20the%20world.%20After%20gaining%20Independence%20in%201947%2C%20India's%20economic%20landscape%20underwent%20significant%20changes%2C%20including%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20Indian%20Rupee's%20relationship%20with%20the%20US%20Dollar.%20Initially%2C%20the%20Indian%20Rupee%20was%20pegged%20to%20the%20British%20Pound%2C%20but%20in%201950%2C%20a%20shift%20occurred%2C%20linking%20it%20to%20the%20US%20Dollar%20under%20the%20Bretton%20Woods%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20time%20when%20a%20dollar%20could%20be%20bought%20at%20less%20than%20five%20rupees.%20However%2C%20one%20dollar%20in%20rupees%20in%202024%20is%20around%20Rs%2083.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere's%20a%20brief%20history%20of%20the%20journey%20of%20rupee%20and%20its%20exchange%20rate%20against%20dollar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbesindia.com%2Farticle%2Fexplainers%2F1-usd-to-inr-history%2F88635%2F1%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20British%20colonia%20era%20impacted%20the%20country's%20economy%20as%20well%20as%20its%20currency.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20the%20value%20of%20rupee%20was%20directly%20influence%20by%20the%20economic%20conditions%20in%20Britain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Great%20Depression%20of%20the%201930s%20broke%20the%20global%20economy%20and%20also%20impacted%20India.%20Since%20the%20rupee%20was%20pegged%20to%20the%20Pound%2C%20it%20was%20much%20stronger%20compare%20to%20the%20dollar.%20As%20per%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20one%20Pound%20was%20equivalent%20to%20Rs%2013.37%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20expectation%20that%20one%20dollar%20must%20have%20been%20worth%20Rs%204.16%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Independence%2C%20government%20intervened%20from%20time%20to%20time%20to%20manage%20any%20fluctuations%20in%20rate.%20During%20the%20first%20few%20decades%20USD%20to%20rupee%20exchange%20rate%20remained%20relatively%20stable.%20However%2C%20wars%20with%20China%20and%20Pakistan%20disrupted%20the%20stability%20of%20the%20rupee%20and%20also%20strained%20India's%20foreign%20exchange%20reserves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20the%20oil%20crisis%20in%20the%201970s%20that%20led%20to%20inflationary%20pressures%20and%20increased%20the%20dollar%20rate.%20A%20number%20of%20adjustments%20and%20policy%20decisions%20by%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20slowly%20moved%20the%20rupee%20from%20a%20par%20value%20method%20to%20a%20pegged%20system%20and%20then%20to%20a%20basket%20peg%20by%201975.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20liberalisation%20of%201991%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20crucial%20turning%20point%20in%20India's%20economic%20history%20and%20significantly%20impacted%20the%20rupee-dollar%20exchange%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20reforms%20shifted%20from%20a%20fixed%20exchange%20rate%20system%20to%20a%20more%20flexible%20one.%20The%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said%20that%20the%20rupee%20was%20partially%20converted%20to%20the%20current%20account%2C%20allowing%20for%20greater%20flexibility%20in%20exchange%20rate%20determination.%20This%20changed%20the%20exchange%20rate%20and%20value%20of%20%241%20was%20Rs%2035.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20year%202000%2C%20the%20dollar%20rate%20increased%20to%20Rs%2045.%20Global%20events%20such%20as%20the%20Asian%20financial%20crisis%20and%20India's%20efforts%20to%20modernise%20its%20economy%20played%20pivotal%20roles%20in%20shaping%20the%20US%20dollar%20to%20rupee%20exchange%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202001%2C%20the%20exchange%20rate%20was%2047%2C%20weakened%20to%20around%20Rs%2075%20in%202020%2C%20and%20fell%20further%20to%20about%20Rs%2080%20in%202023.%20A%20number%20of%20factors%20played%20a%20role%20in%20these%20fluctuations%2C%20such%20and%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis%20and%20most%20recently%2C%20Covid-19.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705558560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fkv2abom_indian-rupee-history-1200_625x300_18_January_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fthere-was-a-time-when-1-dollar-was-less-than-rs-5-know-history-4884685%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20liberalisation%20of%201991%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20crucial%20turning%20point%20in%20India's%20economic%20history%20and%20significantly%20impacted%20the%20rupee-dollar%20exchange%20rate.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fthere-was-a-time-when-1-dollar-was-less-than-rs-5-know-history-4884685%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22She%20started%20as%20a%20flight%20attendant%20at%20age%2020.%20Now%2C%20she's%20just%20been%20named%20Japan%20Airlines'%20first%20female%20president.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mitsuko%20Tottori%3B%20japan%20airlines%20plane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a899006979d73718243336%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJapan%20Airlines'%20first-ever%20female%20president%20Mitsuko%20Tottori%20worked%20as%20cabin%20crew%20for%2020%20years%20with%20the%20company.%3Cp%3EMarcio%20Rodrigo%20Machado%2FS3studio%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJapan%20Airlines%20named%20a%20woman%20as%20president%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20its%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMitsuko%20Tottori%20worked%20as%20a%20flight%20attendant%20with%20JAL%20for%2020%20years%20before%20becoming%20a%20manager.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETottori's%20appointment%20comes%20after%20JetBlue%20announced%20its%20first-ever%20female%20CEO%20on%20January%209.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20president%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-airlines-crash-swiss-cheese-holes-may-explain-collision-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJapan%20Airlines%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20helm%20the%20top%20job%20at%20the%20company%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpress.jal.co.jp%2Fen%2Fitems%2Fuploads%2Fe8d96b2d9c086a8012a8f2ef68905ae54dd34695.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20airline%20announced%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMitsuko%20Tottori%2C%2059%2C%20will%20take%20over%20as%20president%20on%20April%201%2C%20nine%20months%20after%20she%20was%20promoted%20to%20senior%20managing%20executive%20officer%2C%20according%20to%20JAL's%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETottori%20first%20joined%20the%20company%20in%201985%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20flight%20attendant%20for%2020%20years%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jal.com%2Fen%2Fcompany%2Fdirectors%2Fd_mitsuko_tottori.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20her%20company%20profile.%3C%2Fa%3E%20In%202005%2C%20Tottori%20became%20JAL's%20manager%20for%20its%20cabin%20attendant%20department%20and%20was%20promoted%20to%20senior%20management%20in%202013%2C%20per%20the%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETottori%20will%20replace%20Yuji%20Akasaka%2C%20the%20airline's%20president%20since%20June%202018%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jal.com%2Fen%2Fcompany%2Fdirectors%2Fd_yuji_akasaka.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Akasaka's%20company%