D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a8739fdcdb354a985876b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20man%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20his%20house%2C%20which%20was%20damaged%20by%206.9%20magnitude%20earthquake%2C%20at%20the%20Himalayan%20Mangan%20village%20in%20India.%3Cp%3EStringer%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20doesn't%20mean%20a%20giant%20crack%20is%20going%20to%20open%20across%20the%20surface%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdalai-lama-suck-my-tongue-boy-innocent-tibetan-leader-says-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETibet%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Rather%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20more%20going%20on%20deep%20beneath%20the%20surface%20than%20scientists%20realized.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20this%20%26quot%3Bslab%20tear%26quot%3B%20under%20Tibet%20could%20drive%20hazardous%20earthquakes%20in%20the%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20has%20not%20yet%20undergone%20peer%20review%2C%20but%20it%20was%20presented%20at%20the%20meeting%20of%20the%20American%20Geophysical%20Union%20in%20December%2C%20and%20a%20pre-print%20version%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fessopenarchive.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.22541%2Fessoar.170000377.75686509%2Fv1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20published%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20didn't%20know%20continents%20could%20behave%20this%20way%20and%20that%20is%2C%20for%20solid%20earth%20science%2C%20pretty%20fundamental%2C%26quot%3B%20Douwe%20van%20Hinsbergen%2C%20an%20Utrecht%20University%20geodynamicist%20who%20was%20not%20involved%20in%20the%20research%2C%20told%20the%20magazine%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fcontent%2Farticle%2Ftectonic-plate-under-tibet-may-be-splitting-two%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EScience%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimon%20Klemperer%2C%20a%20geophysicist%20at%20Stanford%20University%2C%20worked%20with%20colleagues%20at%20three%20Chinese%20research%20institutions%20to%20piece%20together%20this%20picture%20of%20the%20plates.%20They%20studied%20earthquake%20waves%20that%20passed%20through%20the%20deep%20layers%20below%2C%20examined%20the%20locations%20of%20earthquakes%20under%20Tibet%2C%20and%20analyzed%20gases%20rising%20into%20hot%20springs%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20speculate%20that%20this%20slab%20tear%20may%20divide%20the%20mountain%20chain%20along%20its%20length%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20scientists%20wrote%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagu.confex.com%2Fagu%2Ffm23%2Fmeetingapp.cgi%2FPaper%2F1238166%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esummary%20of%20their%20findings%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Himalayas%20run%20along%20the%20southern%20edge%20of%20Tibet%2C%20which%20sits%20on%20a%20plateau%20about%2013%2C000%20ft%20above%20sea%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20no%20direct%20link%20has%20been%20documented%2C%20these%20deep%20shifts%20in%20the%20earth%20might%20affect%20earthquakes%20near%20the%20surface%2C%20van%20Hinsbergen%20told%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20have%20long%20thought%20this%20type%20of%20tearing%20could%20happen%20when%20continental%20plates%20collide%2C%20but%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20it's%20been%20%26quot%3Bcaught%20in%20the%20act%2C%26quot%3B%20van%20Hinsbergen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftibet-maybe-splitting-apart-himalayan-mountains-grow-tectonic-plates-study-2024-1%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705546608000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65a8507d6979d73718242948%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftibet-maybe-splitting-apart-himalayan-mountains-grow-tectonic-plates-study-2024-1%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Himalayas%20continue%20to%20grow%20as%20the%20Indian%20and%20Eurasian%20plates%20collide%2C%20but%20scientists%20say%20the%20process%20may%20be%20peeling%20apart%20the%20plate%20beneath%20Tibet.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis%2CMorgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A17%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftibet-maybe-splitting-apart-himalayan-mountains-grow-tectonic-plates-study-2024-1%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Names%20Of%2010%20Countries%20With%20Highest%20Gold%20Reserves%20Out%2C%20Know%20India's%20Rank%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EGold%20reserves%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20ensuring%20the%20economic%20stability%20of%20a%20nation%2C%20serving%20as%20a%20dependable%20store%20of%20value%2C%20especially%20in%20times%20of%20financial%20uncertainties.%20The%20gold%20standard%2C%20widely%20adopted%20in%20the%20late%201800s%20and%20a%20substantial%20part%20of%20the%201900s%2C%20involved%20countries%20pegging%20the%20value%20of%20their%20paper%20currency%20to%20gold%20by%20setting%20a%20fixed%20exchange%20rate%20between%20their%20currency%20and%20a%20specific%20quantity%20of%20gold%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Essentially%2C%20each%20unit%20of%20currency%20issued%20had%20an%20equivalent%20value%20in%20gold%2C%20allowing%20individuals%20to%20exchange%20their%20paper%20money%20for%20real%20gold%20at%20this%20established%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20being%20officially%20abandoned%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20many%20countries%20still%20maintain%20gold%20reserves%20and%20now%20the%20demand%20for%20these%20reserves%20is%20rising%20due%20to%20growing%20economic%20uncertainty.%20Central%20banks%20are%20once%20again%20showing%20a%20preference%20for%20gold%20as%20the%20primary%20safe-haven%20asset.%20Gold%20reserves%20remain%20instrumental%20in%20influencing%20a%20country's%20creditworthiness%20and%20overall%20economic%20position%2C%20even%20as%20the%20modern%20economic%20landscape%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20a%20list%20of%20the%20top%2010%20countries%20with%20the%20largest%20gold%20reserves%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20USA%20has%20the%20world's%20highest%20gold%20reserves%20of%208%2C1336.46%20tonnes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbesindia.com%2Farticle%2Fexplainers%2Fgold-reserves-by-country%2F90127%2F1%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EGermany%20has%20the%20second-highest%20gold%20reserve%20of%203%2C352.65%20tonnes.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EItaly%20has%20the%20third-highest%20gold%20reserve%20of%202%2C451.84%20tonnes%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFrance%20has%20gold%20reserves%20of%202%2C436.88%20tonnes%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWith%20gold%20reserves%20of%202%2C332.74%20tonnes%2C%20Russia%20is%20ranked%20in%20fifth%20place%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EChina%2C%20an%20upper%20middle-income%20nation%2C%20has%20the%20highest%20gold%20reserves%20of%202%2C191.53%20tonnes%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESwitzerland%20has%20gold%20reserves%20of%201%2C040.00%20tonnes%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EJapan%20has%20gold%20reserves%20of%20845.97%20tonnes%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIndia%20is%20ranked%209th%20on%20the%20list%20with%20800.78%20tonnes%20of%20reserved%20gold%2C%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20Netherlands%20has%20gold%20reserves%20of%20612.45%20tonnes%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EKnow%20why%20countries%20have%20a%20gold%20reserve%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20not%20one%2C%20but%20several%20reasons%20why%20countries%20maintain%20gold%20reserves.%20First%20and%20foremost%2C%20gold%20is%20recognised%20as%20a%20stable%20and%20dependable%20store%20of%20value.%20By%20holding%20gold%2C%20countries%20can%20instil%20confidence%20in%20their%20economic%20stability%2C%20particularly%20in%20times%20of%20financial%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20gold%20has%20historically%20contributed%20to%20supporting%20the%20value%20of%20a%20country's%20currency.%20While%20the%20gold%20standard%20is%20no%20longer%20widely%20practised%2C%20some%20countries%20still%20perceive%20gold%20reserves%20as%20a%20method%20to%20maintain%20currency%20stability%2C%20%3Cem%3EForbes%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiversification%20is%20another%20reason.%20Gold%2C%20being%20a%20tangible%20asset%2C%20enables%20countries%20to%20diversify%20their%20overall%20portfolio%20by%20incorporating%20it%20into%20their%20reserves.%20This%20diversification%20helps%20mitigate%20risks%20associated%20with%20fluctuations%20in%20the%20value%20of%20other%20assets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20attractiveness%20of%20gold%20is%20heightened%20by%20its%20inverse%20correlation%20with%20the%20US%20dollar.%20When%20the%20value%20of%20the%20dollar%20decreases%2C%20gold%20tends%20to%20appreciate%2C%20allowing%20central%20banks%20to%20protect%20their%20reserves%20during%20periods%20of%20market%20volatility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGold%20reserves%20also%20play%20a%20role%20in%20international%20trade%20and%20finance.%20Some%20countries%20employ%20gold%20to%20settle%20trade%20imbalances%20or%20as%20collateral%20for%20loans.%20The%20existence%20of%20gold%20reserves%20can%20enhance%20a%20country's%20creditworthiness%20and%20influence%20its%20standing%20in%20the%20global%20economic%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20gold%20functions%20as%20a%20hedge%20during%20crises.%20Its%20value%20often%20rises%20amid%20economic%20downturns%20or%20geopolitical%20uncertainties%2C%20protecting%20against%20inflation%20and%20currency%20devaluation.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705546440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fu5ue8fj_gold-generic_625x300_18_January_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fnames-of-10-countries-with-highest-gold-reserves-revealed-know-indias-rank-4883838%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Despite%20being%20officially%20abandoned%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20many%20countries%20still